headline: DRI Q4 Deep Dive: Menu Innovation and Delivery Offset Cost Pressures, Guidance Maintained
summary: Restaurant company Darden (NYSE:DRI) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 7.3% year on year to $3.10 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.08 per share was 0.8% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
